Transcription.Text: Yet it must in fact be of the utmost importance in many cases. Pressure has been suggested as having some influence upon migration, espaecially of Calanus. But experiments expressly designed to test this have not revealed any change in the behaviour of this species under pressures up to the equivalent of 20 meters depth.
